Notes about build files in the "make" directory
-----------------------------------------------

BUILD SYSTEM
------------

Makefile-ace    - GNU Makefile for building the ACE compiler.
                  Requires GNU Make 3.80+ and ADE shell environment.
                  Usage: make -f Makefile-ace
                         make -f Makefile-ace V=1    (verbose)
                         make -f Makefile-ace clean  (clean build)

Makefile-lib    - GNU Makefile for building the runtime libraries.
                  Builds db.lib and startup.lib using vbcc/vasm toolchain.
                  Usage: make -f Makefile-lib
                         make -f Makefile-lib V=1    (verbose)
                         make -f Makefile-lib clean  (clean build)
                         make -f Makefile-lib help   (show all targets)

See src/lib/README.md for details about the runtime libraries.
